Springs Valley Yearbook
September 8 at 12:15 PM ·

On September 15, 2020 we will be having picture day here at Springs Valley Jr/Sr High School for students in grades 6-12. Students who are virtual or are enrolled in the Academy can have their photos taken on this day as well. Students would need to arrive between 8:00 a.m. and 10:30 a.m. to have your photo taken. Students will be required to sign in at the High School Office and proceed immediately to the auditorium where you will again sign-in when entering and sign-out when exiting the auditorium. You will then go back to the office and sign-out and then leave the school campus going back to your regular school day routine. This tracking will help us with attendance for virtual students.

*No money is needed for photos on picture day.

Supply List for 8th Grade:
3 Composition Notebooks 100 sheet count with cardboard cover (will be collected and kept in the classroom for daily use, 2 for English and 1 for Science)
2 bottles of glue (English and Science)
1 three prong pocket folder (Science)
Highlighters (English)

English and Science classes will be using interactive notebooks throughout the year. Students may want to bring scissors and colored pencils/pens. These supplies are optional.

For other classes, make sure you have paper, pencils, and folders (or other organizational storage). **Some classes may require additional school supplies after school begins. We look forward to seeing everyone in a few weeks!

We will be having a drive-through pick-up of prom favors and crowning our royalty on Saturday, June 13th. This will take place at the circle in front of the main high school doors.

June 10 at 11:45 AM ·

SV Community,
After much consideration, along with a review of state guidelines and consultation with local health officials and county superintendents, we have decided to cancel prom this year. Orleans and Paoli Schools have also cancelled their proms. This decision was not made lightly. However, given current circumstances it is the best option to comply with local and state guidelines. Graduates of the Class of 2020 are invited to attend the 2021 prom free of charge if they so choose. We will be refunding guest fees.

post_text:
Media Release:
Southern Indiana Small Schools Coalition

Nine southern Indiana school districts are joining forces to discuss problems and potential solutions related to the Covid-19 Pandemic. A joint focus will be placed on re-entry procedures for safe and effective “in-person” instruction for the 2020-21 school year. The coalition currently includes administrators from East Washington School Corporation, Salem Community Schools, Paoli Community Schools, Springs Valley Community Schools, Orleans Community Schools, North Harrison Community School Corporation, South Harrison Community School Corporation, Scott County School District 2 and Lanesville Community Schools. The coalition will expand membership based upon interest from other districts. Representatives from Butler University will contribute as thought partners exploring strategies for the safe re-entry of students and staff for the fall semester.
text:
Media Release:
Southern Indiana Small Schools Coalition

Nine southern Indiana school districts are joining forces to discuss problems and potential solutions related to the Covid-19 Pandemic. A joint focus will be placed on re-entry procedures for safe and effective “in-person” instruction for the 2020-21 school year. The coalition currently includes administrators from East Washington School Corporation, Salem Community Schools, Paoli Community Schools, Springs Valley Community Schools, Orleans Community Schools, North Harrison Community School Corporation, South Harrison Community School Corporation, Scott County School District 2 and Lanesville Community Schools. The coalition will expand membership based upon interest from other districts. Representatives from Butler University will contribute as thought partners exploring strategies for the safe re-entry of students and staff for the fall semester.

The Indiana Retired Teachers Association today (IRTA) has launched a new "Call & Learn" hotline to help kids learning at home.

K-12 students can call a toll-free number for homework help.

Students and parents can (877) 45-STUDY (877-457-8839) to request assistance from a volunteer educator. Once you call, you will have to give some information including the student's grade level.

The hotline is open weekdays from 1 p.m. to 5 p.m. ET.

Any retired Indiana educator interested in volunteering for the program can contact IRTA at teacherhelp@retiredteachers.org or or call (888) 454-9333.

Svhs Principal
April 14 at 8:19 AM ·

SV Community,
We have set a make-up date for prom on Saturday, July 11 in the JH gym with a start time to be announced later. That time will be determined by other factors which can not be planned at this time.
If state regulations are not lifted by an appropriate date, we will cancel prom for this year. Graduating seniors will be allowed to attend prom in 2021 free of charge.
We have postponed the 2020 graduation ceremony until Saturday, July 18 starting at 6:00 in the HS gym. This will be a traditional commencement as long as COVID-19 regulations are lifted by that time.
If regulations are not lifted, we will be performing a virtual drive-through celebration. Students and families will drive up and remain in cars with our students receiving their diplomas from administrators and the school board. Other plans with this option will be organized as time gets closer.
Thank you all for your support. We are going to do the best we can for our seniors.

Good afternoon,

The Essentials Project has helped serve over 130 requests from students this year. We've also helped several students with clothing and food essentials. We couldn't have had this success without the school staff and community of Springs Valley. Your support has really made this project exceed our expectations. Our mission is to enhance a student’s life by providing basic hygiene necessities, and I think we are doing that!

Please remind students about the Essentials Project. We have additional options available to help students with haircuts, showers, laundry, and food. The link for requests can be accessed on the school website or on the student Chromebook bookmark page.

If you have any questions, please let us know. Thank you so much for your support of this program. It is truly making a difference.

post_text:
Mrs. Connie Reed’s economics students are currently studying the unit over “Budgeting”. During the unit, the students were directed to create a grocery list for 1 week that would fit into their personal budgets. The students then took a field trip to the Jay C Store in West Baden to price their items. Once the pricing was completed, the students turned in their grocery list assignment.

The students’ previously studied the unit on “Philanthropy” and the importance of giving back to our community. Upon completion of the first assignment, the students returned to shopping and each student purchased $5 worth of grocery items for the school’s blessing box; the students were each involved in stocking the box with their purchased items. This blessing box serves all of Springs Valley’s students; it is located in the hallway near the PACT office. Any student may access the box at the end of the day to take items as needed. After the service-learning field trip, the students said that it felt good to give back to our community.
